      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" width=\"900\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542231739/PxrCamera_Abberation.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330717514&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=900&amp;height=506\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542231739/PxrCamera_Abberation.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330717514&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"720\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542231751\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"PxrCamera_Abberation.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542231739\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"e140ef80-7c7f-4c04-8354-312086d18cbe\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542231739/PxrCamera_Abberation.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330717514&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542231739/PxrCamera_Abberation.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330717514&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=900&amp;height=506 1x\"></span><p><strong>Transverse</strong></p><p>Transverse (or lateral) chromatic aberration. This specifies the magnification factors for the red, green, and blue primaries respectively. When unequal, this can produce a tinge which is most pronounced near the image edges. It will increase color noise, however.</p><p><strong>Axial</strong></p><p>Axial (or longitudinal) chromatic aberration. This specifies the chromatic focal shift for the red, green, and blue primaries respectively. When unequal, this can produce a tinge on bokeh and out of focus objects. It will increase color noise, however.</p>"
    }
